attempt T5_WEDDERBURN_LITTLE_CYCLE_2
  target: For every finite division ring D, D is commutative.
  progress:
    let F=Z(D) and choose a maximal subfield K containing F.
    K is finite, hence K^* is cyclic.
    D^* acts by conjugation on maximal subfields; the normalizer N_D*(K^*) controls the conjugacy class of K.
    If N_D*(K^*) is strictly larger than K^*, the induced automorphism action on K should yield centrality constraints.
    If N_D*(K^*)=K^*, the conjugates of K intersect in F on noncentral elements only under an unproved intersection lemma.
  stuck_state:
    Need a closed normalizer/intersection/counting lemma: for maximal subfields K,L of D, prove the required intersection and conjugacy count without citing Wedderburn or cyclic algebra classification.
  next_attack:
    Prove the intersection lemma first: if K and gKg^-1 share a noncentral element, show maximality forces K=gKg^-1 or identify the centralizer as a larger commutative subfield.
  status: BLOCKED-ITERATE-with-new-obstruction